body:
REMReM (REST Mailbox for Registered Messages) is a set of tools that can be used to generate validated Eiffel messages and publish them on a RabbitMQ message bus. They can be run as micro services or as stand-alone CLI versions. For more details on the micro services and the REMReM design, see https://github.com/eiffel-community/eiffel-remrem 

Generate takes a partial message in JSON format, validates it and adds mandatory fields before outputting a complete, valid Eiffel message.

## Compatibility
* JDK 8
* Tomcat 7

## The releases
Binary is relased via [jitPack](https://jitpack.io/#Ericsson/eiffel-remrem-generate).

## Installation
java -jar eiffel-remrem-generate-version.war
or deploy it in tomcat

## Usage CLI (Command Line Interface). 
Examples used here are for the next generation of Eiffel events called semantics which is open source. Please follow [eiffel syntax](https://github.com/eiffel-community/eiffel/tree/master/eiffel-syntax-and-usage) and [eiffel vocabulary](https://github.com/eiffel-community/eiffel/tree/master/eiffel-vocabulary)

java -jar generate.war -h

You passed help flag.

usage: java -jar

-d,--debug                       enable debug traces

-f,--content_file <arg>          message content file

-h,--help                        show help.

-json,--json_content <arg>       json content

-mp,--messaging_protocol <arg>   name of messaging protocol to be used,
                                  e.g. eiffel3, semantics, semantics is used if nothing given

-r,--response_file <arg>         file to store the response in, optional

-t,--message_type <arg>          message type, mandatory if -f or -json
                                  is given
The message type not contain the suffix event but just the event time for example eiffelactivityfinished and not EiffelActivityFinishedEvent.

The message must exist in a json file for example ***EiffelActivityFinishedEvent.json*** might contain following message:<br>
{"msgParams": {
  "meta": {
    "type": "EiffelActivityFinishedEvent",
    "domainId": "example.domain",
    "tags": ["tag1", "tag2"],
    "source": {
      "host": "host",
      "name": "name",
      "uri": "http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.3/",
      "serializer": {
        "groupId": "G",
        "artifactId": "A",
        "version": "V"
      }
    }
  }
},
  "eventParams": {
    "data": {
      "outcome": {
        "conclusion": "TIMED_OUT",
        "description": "Compilation timed out."
      },
      "persistentLogs": [
        {
          "name": "firstLog",
          "uri": "http://myHost.com/firstLog"
        },
        {
          "name": "otherLog",
          "uri": "isbn:0-486-27557-4"
        }
      ]
    },
    "links": {
      "activityExecution": "aaaaaaaa-bbbb-cccc-dddd-eeeeeeeeeee1",
      "causes": ["cause1", "cause2"],
      "flowContext": "flowContext"
    }
  }
}

###With input from the example file shown above and output to a file:

     $ java -jar generate.war -f EiffelActivityFinishedEvent.json -t eiffelactivityfinished -r output.json

Gives:

$cat output.json

